# PH-LLM work-package scope

## Branch rule

- One **WP-LLM-XX** per feature branch (e.g. `feat/wp-llm-01-tokenizer`).
- Wave 0 scaffold (`feat/world-studio-lillm-wave0`) is steward-only; agents resume with a single WP after merge.

## WP boundaries

| WP | Scope | Gate |
|----|-------|------|
| WP-LLM-01 | BPE/byte-level tokenizer + vocab load | smoke roundtrip |
| WP-LLM-02 | Safetensors + GGUF loader (f32/f16; no MoE v1) | load Llama-3.2-1B-class fixture |
| WP-LLM-03 | Transformer graph (attn, ffn, RoPE) | forward vs reference logits ULP |
| WP-LLM-04 | KV-cache + decode loop (`llm_generate`) | greedy decode smoke |
| WP-LLM-05 | CPU perf via `li-ml`/`linalg` matmul | tier-3 bench row |
| WP-LLM-06 | GPU matmul/attention via `@gpu` + LKIR | tier-3 GPU column |
| WP-LLM-07 | HF → safetensors export doc + import CLI | one documented model path |
| WP-LLM-08 | Trusted backend (Ollama/OpenAI) — Wave 2 | audit + `[trusted]` fence |

## Rules

1. **One WP per PR** — do not mix tokenizer with transformer forward in one PR
2. **Stub honesty** — label unimplemented APIs; `li_llm_version() == 0` until WP lands
3. **No PyTorch runtime** — weights via safetensors/GGUF export only
4. **Gate before merge** — each WP must pass its exit smoke/bench
5. **Dependencies** — respect 01→02→03→04 chain
6. **li-native-li-only** — inference logic in `.li`; no new C/Python product helpers

## Exit before PR

1. `./scripts/build.sh` (if compiler touched)
2. `lic check packages/li-llm/li-tests/smoke/` (and `li-studio-ai` if orchestration touched)
3. Update PH-LLM-program.md row status when WP closes
